  "text": "3. (ii) b. To obtain p UE+NE , the following formula was used:p UE+NE = (1−e λ where u t+1 = number of unemployed in period t + 1, u t = number of unemployed in period t and u s t+1 = short term unemployed workers, who are unemployed at date t+1 but held a job at some point during period t. An explanation of how short term unemployment was calculated is to be found in [CITATION_1] , Appendix A. ",
